{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "I am considering the following use cases:\r\n\r\n1. Catkin workspaces installations (currently broken for the need of root perms to install /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh)\r\n1.  System from source installations\r\n1.  Deb package generation\r\n\r\nIn 2 and 3 we want to keep setup.sh into /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh while in 1 we don't want it at all. Another way to control this would be to introduce a building parameter to install it or not, but then magic won't happen anymore automatically for all cases.\r\n\r\n@gerkey do you see any flaw to this hack besides it is just this, a hack?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I am considering the following use cases:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Catkin workspaces installations (currently broken for the need of root perms to install /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh)</li>\n<li>System from source installations</li>\n<li>Deb package generation</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In 2 and 3 we want to keep setup.sh into /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh while in 1 we don't want it at all. Another way to control this would be to introduce a building parameter to install it or not, but then magic won't happen anymore automatically for all cases.</p>\n<p>@gerkey do you see any flaw to this hack besides it is just this, a hack?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Install setup.sh in /usr only if PREFIX is /opt/ros in order to respect catkin ws", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Install setup.sh in /usr only if PREFIX is /opt/ros in order to respect catkin ws</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "I am considering the following use cases:\r\n\r\n1. Catkin workspaces installations (currently broken for the need of root perms to install /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh)\r\n1.  System from source installations\r\n1.  Deb package generation\r\n\r\nIn 2 and 3 we want to keep setup.sh into /usr/share/drcsim/setup.sh while in 1 we don't want it at all. Another way to control this would be to introduce a building paramet